<title>USA: Lucent CFO optimistic on mkt shr in Brazil.</title>
<headline>Lucent CFO optimistic on mkt shr in Brazil.</headline>
<dateline>ST PETERSBURG BEACH, Fla. 1997-03-03</dateline>
<text>
<p>Lucent Technologies Inc chief financial officer Don Peterson said on Monday his telephone equipment-manufacturing group was optimistic about securing a sizeable share of Brazil's spending on telecommunications.</p>
<p>The executive gave no details of the competiton among suppliers in Brazil, but said Lucent, a spinoff from AT&amp;T, saw Latin America as a key growth sector. One key rival is Ericsson, he said.</p>
<p>&quot;The feedback we are getting is very optimistic,&quot; Peterson said at an investors conference sponsored by Raymond James &amp; Associates Inc. &quot;The response there has been very good.&quot;</p>
<p>He said Lucent, a supplier of software, machinery and expertise for telephone companies, mainly in the United States, had scored several recent business victories in Brazil, but declined to give details.</p>
<p>((-- Michael Connor, Miami newsroom 305 374-5013))</p>
